1
00:01:38,993 --> 00:01:40,544
We're ruined!

2
00:01:40,686 --> 00:01:42,320
No more free Wi-Fi.

3
00:01:43,756 --> 00:01:44,756
Hey, Ki-jung!

4
00:01:44,857 --> 00:01:45,924
Yeah?

5
00:01:46,025 --> 00:01:50,095
The woman upstairs
finally put a password on iptime.

6
00:01:50,196 --> 00:01:51,930
A password?

7
00:01:52,031 --> 00:01:53,664
Did you try "123456789"?

8
00:01:53,808 --> 00:01:54,808
Yeah, doesn't work.

9
00:01:54,909 --> 00:01:56,309
Try it in reverse.

10
00:01:56,410 --> 00:01:57,811
I told you, it doesn't work.

11
00:01:57,912 --> 00:02:02,148
Shit! Then no text,
no Ka- Talk, no nothing?

12
00:02:02,249 --> 00:02:03,424
That's right.

13
00:02:04,001 --> 00:02:06,219
Hey, Kim Ki-taek.

14
00:02:06,754 --> 00:02:10,223
Fucking don't pretend to sleep.
What do you think?

15
00:02:10,756 --> 00:02:16,813
Our phones are all shut off...
Wi-Fi is all shut off...

16
00:02:17,348 --> 00:02:20,441
Fucking what's your plan?
Huh?

17
00:02:22,728 --> 00:02:23,962
- Hey, Ki-woo.
- Yes, father?

18
00:02:24,063 --> 00:02:27,990
For Wi-Fi, you have to hold it up high.

19
00:02:29,610 --> 00:02:33,204
Search out every corner.

20
00:02:36,742 --> 00:02:40,795
Damn stink bugs!

21
00:02:41,330 --> 00:02:43,523
Hey, here! I got it!

22
00:02:43,624 --> 00:02:44,941
Really? You got it?

23
00:02:45,042 --> 00:02:46,860
Yeah, you're getting it too?

24
00:02:46,961 --> 00:02:49,612
This one, 'coffee land 2G.'

25
00:02:49,713 --> 00:02:51,698
A new cafe opened up nearby?

26
00:02:51,799 --> 00:02:53,408
Why can't I get it?

27
00:02:53,509 --> 00:02:55,118
Come up here closer.

28
00:02:55,219 --> 00:02:56,519
Hey kids?

29
00:02:56,919 --> 00:02:58,913
- Is it working?
- Yeah.

30
00:02:59,014 --> 00:03:01,566
Then check on Ka-Talk.

31
00:03:02,101 --> 00:03:04,443
Pizza Time said they'd contact me.

32
00:03:04,979 --> 00:03:06,362
Ok, hold on.

33
00:03:06,897 --> 00:03:09,240
Here it is. Pizza Time.

34
00:03:12,278 --> 00:03:16,014
Wow, check this out!

35
00:03:16,115 --> 00:03:19,309
At this speed, I think
we can finish all these today!

36
00:03:19,410 --> 00:03:20,643
We're getting paid today, right?

37
00:03:20,744 --> 00:03:24,213
- She does it standing.
- She's a pro!

38
00:03:24,373 --> 00:03:27,341
What's that? Fumigation?

39
00:03:29,003 --> 00:03:30,487
They still do that kind of thing?

40
00:03:30,588 --> 00:03:31,529
Guess so.

41
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:32,405
Shut the window.

42
00:03:32,506 --> 00:03:34,991
Leave it alone.
We'll get free indoor fumigation.

43
00:03:35,092 --> 00:03:36,784
And get rid of the stink bugs.

44
00:03:36,885 --> 00:03:39,770
Right, too many stink bugs these days.

45
00:03:41,849 --> 00:03:44,191
Oh, that smell!

46
00:03:46,729 --> 00:03:48,463
I told you to shut it!

47
00:03:48,564 --> 00:03:50,656
Should I shut it?

48
00:04:01,493 --> 00:04:03,294
What's the problem exactly?

49
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:07,148
For example, have a look here.

50
00:04:07,249 --> 00:04:09,592
You see this god-awful line?

51
00:04:10,127 --> 00:04:11,986
And why is there a crease here? Huh?

52
00:04:12,087 --> 00:04:13,738
Why is this sticking out?

53
00:04:13,839 --> 00:04:16,432
That means you didn't finish folding it.

54
00:04:17,468 --> 00:04:21,246
On inspection, 1 out of 4 were in this condition.

55
00:04:21,347 --> 00:04:23,898
Roughly, 1 out of 4 are rejects.

56
00:04:27,061 --> 00:04:30,947
So, you're really docking 10% off our pay?

57
00:04:31,273 --> 00:04:34,951
Considering the fail rate,
the penalty is very minor, don't you think?

58
00:04:35,819 --> 00:04:39,080
But, our pay is so low already!
Aren't you being too harsh?

59
00:04:41,116 --> 00:04:42,116
You look here.

60
00:04:42,217 --> 00:04:45,019
This is not a minor issue.

61
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:50,548
Do you know how much damage
these faulty boxes cause to our brand image?

62
00:04:50,584 --> 00:04:53,812
Brand? You don't even have
a proper box folder, shit!

63
00:04:53,922 --> 00:04:55,055
What did you say?!

64
00:04:56,340 --> 00:04:57,440
Boss.

65
00:04:58,425 --> 00:04:59,659
This is all because of that guy, isn't it?

66
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,618
What are you talking about?

67
00:05:00,719 --> 00:05:04,581
That other part-time help,
he went AWOL, right?

68
00:05:04,682 --> 00:05:07,792
Just when you got that huge, important
group order from that church.

69
00:05:07,893 --> 00:05:11,028
How do you know these details?

70
00:05:11,188 --> 00:05:12,755
Who told you?

71
00:05:12,856 --> 00:05:14,841
My sister knows the guy.

72
00:05:14,942 --> 00:05:19,470
He's always been a bit strange.
He has a bad reputation around here.

73
00:05:19,571 --> 00:05:21,664
Therefore, Boss.

74
00:05:22,199 --> 00:05:24,225
The 10% penalty,
we'll accept it.

75
00:05:24,326 --> 00:05:25,310
In return...

76
00:05:25,411 --> 00:05:26,752
In return?

77
00:05:26,912 --> 00:05:29,397
Any thought of hiring
new part-time help?

78
00:05:29,498 --> 00:05:32,883
Sis, we need more hired help!

79
00:05:33,419 --> 00:05:36,846
Fire that other part-timer.
Hand him the termination penalty.

80
00:05:37,631 --> 00:05:40,998
I'll come for the formal interview tomorrow.
What time works best best for you?

81
00:05:41,051 --> 00:05:42,393
Hold on a minute.

82
00:05:43,012 --> 00:05:45,271
I need to think about this.

83
00:05:45,891 --> 00:05:49,773
Then, let's start with the
payment for these boxes.

84
00:05:55,610 --> 00:05:59,079
So we've all gathered here today...

85
00:05:59,361 --> 00:06:02,722
to celebrate the partial
reconnection of our phones

86
00:06:02,823 --> 00:06:06,643
and the bountiful Wi-Fi!

87
00:06:06,744 --> 00:06:10,296
That bastard !
So early in the evening!

88
00:06:10,831 --> 00:06:14,525
Why haven't you put up the
'No Urinating' sign?

89
00:06:14,626 --> 00:06:15,276
I told you to!

90
00:06:15,377 --> 00:06:19,764
No, a sign like that only encourages
them...those drunkards.

91
00:06:20,299 --> 00:06:22,075
At least yell at him!

92
00:06:22,176 --> 00:06:23,809
No, don't shout.

93
00:06:23,927 --> 00:06:26,062
"Please don't piss!"
Fuck!

94
00:06:27,598 --> 00:06:30,691
Huh?
Is that Min-hyuk oppa?

95
00:06:31,226 --> 00:06:33,294
Mister, what are you doing?
That's not the toilet.

96
00:06:33,395 --> 00:06:34,712
That is Min-hyuk.

97
00:06:34,813 --> 00:06:36,881
Hey, punk!

98
00:06:36,982 --> 00:06:40,201
What... what are you staring at?

99
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:43,871
Come over here, you little shit.

100
00:06:45,491 --> 00:06:47,958
Get a fucking grip!

101
00:06:48,994 --> 00:06:51,020
Your friend has spunk!

102
00:06:51,121 --> 00:06:54,190
University students have
real spirit. Spirit!

103
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:55,233
Unlike you, big brother.

104
00:06:55,334 --> 00:06:58,736
But, is he coming here?
Were you expecting him?

105
00:06:58,837 --> 00:06:59,937
No.

106
00:07:00,047 --> 00:07:01,072
Hello!

107
00:07:01,173 --> 00:07:02,807
Min-hyuk, you've come!

108
00:07:02,950 --> 00:07:03,950
Hey, what's up?

109
00:07:04,051 --> 00:07:04,826
Have you been well, sir?

110
00:07:04,927 --> 00:07:07,620
- Of course.
- Hey, what's the ocassion?

111
00:07:07,721 --> 00:07:09,313
I texted you.
You didn't see it?

112
00:07:09,848 --> 00:07:10,915
So sorry... during your meal.

113
00:07:11,019 --> 00:07:12,211
No, no, we weren't eating.

114
00:07:12,309 --> 00:07:14,585
- You've been well, Ki-jung?
- Yeah, and you?

115
00:07:14,686 --> 00:07:17,422
You should've asked to meet up.
Why come all the way here?

116
00:07:17,523 --> 00:07:18,256
Because of this.

117
00:07:18,357 --> 00:07:21,217
This is for you,
but it's so darn heavy.

118
00:07:21,318 --> 00:07:23,619
Really? Put it down here.

119
00:07:25,656 --> 00:07:27,265
Wow, what is this?

120
00:07:27,366 --> 00:07:28,933
I told my grandfather that
I'm seeing Ki-woo

121
00:07:29,034 --> 00:07:32,294
and he insisted that
I take this to him.

122
00:07:36,834 --> 00:07:39,009
Wow, is this an artscape stone?

123
00:07:40,128 --> 00:07:41,988
You can also
call this a zen stone.

124
00:07:42,089 --> 00:07:43,781
Wow, you know!

125
00:07:43,882 --> 00:07:47,910
My grandpa has collected these stones
since his military academy days.

126
00:07:48,011 --> 00:07:51,539
Now downstairs, upstairs,
living room, the study...

127
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,624
they're all filled with these.

128
00:07:53,725 --> 00:07:57,587
This stone is said to bring material fortune
and promotion to the family...

129
00:07:57,688 --> 00:07:59,029
Hey, Min-hyuk!

130
00:07:59,189 --> 00:08:02,300
This is really symbolic!

131
00:08:02,401 --> 00:08:05,720
For sure! Truly, this is very timely.

132
00:08:05,821 --> 00:08:06,512
Isn't it?

133
00:08:06,613 --> 00:08:10,666
Please relay our deepest
gratitude to your grandfather.

134
00:08:11,201 --> 00:08:12,960
You could've brought
something to eat.

135
00:08:22,754 --> 00:08:25,907
Hey, what was that called?
Artscape stone?

136
00:08:26,008 --> 00:08:27,325
You collect those rocks too?

137
00:08:27,426 --> 00:08:33,392
Hey, thanks to that rock, I got to
see your parents. They looked healthy.

138
00:08:33,724 --> 00:08:37,692
They're plenty healthy,
just out of work.

139
00:08:39,812 --> 00:08:43,178
Is Ki-jung also home bound these days?
Not taking classes?

140
00:08:43,358 --> 00:08:47,462
It's not that she doesn't want to.
It's that she can't.

141
00:08:54,995 --> 00:08:56,587
She's cute, huh?

142
00:08:57,497 --> 00:08:59,774
Wow, is that her?
The one you're tutoring?

143
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:02,318
Park Da-hye.
High school sophomore.

144
00:09:02,419 --> 00:09:05,804
Why don't you take my place
as her English tutor?

145
00:09:06,073 --> 00:09:07,073
What are you talking about?

146
00:09:07,174 --> 00:09:09,683
It's tutoring for a rich family.
They pay very well.

147
00:09:10,719 --> 00:09:11,828
And, she's a good kid.

148
00:09:11,929 --> 00:09:15,314
While I'm studying abroad,
take good care of her.

149
00:09:15,849 --> 00:09:19,210
What about your close
university friends?

150
00:09:19,311 --> 00:09:22,905
Why ask a deadbeat like me?

151
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,782
Why do you think?

152
00:09:25,317 --> 00:09:27,426
Even the thought of it makes me sick.

153
00:09:27,527 --> 00:09:31,681
My wolf-like bastard classmates
fawning all over Da-hye?

154
00:09:31,782 --> 00:09:34,124
It's revolting.

155
00:09:39,665 --> 00:09:41,131
You into her?

156
00:09:46,171 --> 00:09:48,347
Hey, I'm serious.

157
00:09:49,383 --> 00:09:53,769
Year after next, when she enters university,
I'm going to officially ask her out.

158
00:09:53,887 --> 00:09:55,663
Until then, take good care of her.

159
00:09:55,764 --> 00:10:00,276
If it's you, I can leave with trust.

160
00:10:01,812 --> 00:10:04,488
Thanks for trusting me, but...

161
00:10:04,606 --> 00:10:08,450
do you want me to
pretend I'm a university student?

162
00:10:09,987 --> 00:10:12,955
Ki-woo, think about it.

163
00:10:13,490 --> 00:10:16,893
Two years before and after
your military service

164
00:10:16,994 --> 00:10:19,312
you took the university entrance exam 4 times.

165
00:10:19,413 --> 00:10:22,464
Grammar, vocabulary,
composition, conversation...

166
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,483
Honestly, when it comes to English

167
00:10:24,584 --> 00:10:28,929
you can teach it 10 times better than those
alcohol binging college pricks.

168
00:10:30,465 --> 00:10:33,058
- I guess so.
- Sure!

169
00:10:33,218 --> 00:10:36,913
But, will that family accept me?
I'm not even a university student.

170
00:10:37,014 --> 00:10:38,539
We'll just BS a little.

171
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:42,776
It'll be alright! First of all,
you're going on my recommendation, and...

172
00:10:43,312 --> 00:10:46,488
how should I describe her mother...?

173
00:10:48,525 --> 00:10:49,926
The madame's a bit simple.

174
00:10:50,027 --> 00:10:51,177
Young and simple.

175
00:10:51,278 --> 00:10:52,411
Simple?

176
00:10:52,946 --> 00:10:54,347
What do you mean?

177
00:10:54,448 --> 00:10:58,709
I don't know... Anyway, all's good.
It's been good for me.

178
00:10:59,228 --> 00:11:00,228
So you're doing this, ok?

179
00:11:00,329 --> 00:11:02,129
Ok, then.

180
00:11:03,165 --> 00:11:07,068
Hey, I hear Ki-jung is very
talented with her hands.

181
00:11:07,169 --> 00:11:11,364
...good with things like Photoshop.

182
00:11:11,465 --> 00:11:15,576
With skills like this, why are you
rejected to art schools every time?

183
00:11:15,677 --> 00:11:17,311
Wanna die?

184
00:11:19,473 --> 00:11:21,624
Excuse me, it's non-smoking here.

185
00:11:21,725 --> 00:11:23,125
Yeah, sure. Give me that.

186
00:11:23,226 --> 00:11:24,401
Ok.

187
00:11:28,732 --> 00:11:31,700
Now the finishing touch ...in scarlet red.

188
00:11:33,236 --> 00:11:37,640
Wow, I wonder if Seoul National University
has a major in document forgery.

189
00:11:37,741 --> 00:11:41,102
Ki-jung would be admitted
top of her class!

190
00:11:41,203 --> 00:11:43,896
So true, huh?
Her skills!

191
00:11:43,997 --> 00:11:49,510
Our boy's going for a job interview and
no words of encouragement?

192
00:11:50,045 --> 00:11:51,145
Son!

193
00:11:52,089 --> 00:11:55,057
I'm proud of you.

194
00:11:55,175 --> 00:11:56,275
Father!

195
00:11:57,177 --> 00:12:00,413
I don't think of this
as forgery or crime.

196
00:12:00,514 --> 00:12:02,498
Because, for sure, I'm going to
this university next year.

197
00:12:02,599 --> 00:12:06,085
So, you've got a plan!

198
00:12:06,186 --> 00:12:10,364
I think of it as having produced
this document just earlier.

199
00:12:10,364 --> 00:12:40,364
<b>Subtitle | www.movieddl.me</b>

200
00:12:45,517 --> 00:12:46,817
Who is it?

201
00:12:47,352 --> 00:12:49,170
Are you... Da-hye's mother?
How do you do?

202
00:12:49,271 --> 00:12:51,047
I'm here on teacher
Min-hyuk's recommendation.

203
00:12:51,148 --> 00:12:53,282
Oh, right.
Come on in.

204
00:12:54,317 --> 00:12:55,417
Thank you.

205
00:13:27,350 --> 00:13:28,609
Hello!

206
00:13:29,352 --> 00:13:30,753
How do you do, Madame?

207
00:13:30,854 --> 00:13:34,281
I'm just someone who
works here. Come this way.

208
00:13:34,816 --> 00:13:36,425
The garden is so nice.

209
00:13:36,526 --> 00:13:38,160
The interior is nice, too.

210
00:13:38,695 --> 00:13:41,980
You know the architect
Nam-goong? He's very famous.

211
00:13:42,081 --> 00:13:44,792
This is the house
that he lived in.

212
00:13:46,953 --> 00:13:49,171
He built all this himself.

213
00:13:52,209 --> 00:13:57,179
Now... as you can see,
this is just a family home with children.

214
00:13:57,714 --> 00:13:58,814
This way.

215
00:14:01,218 --> 00:14:03,585
Please sit here and wait.
I'll bring her right up.

216
00:14:03,686 --> 00:14:04,786
Yes.

217
00:14:23,359 --> 00:14:24,576
Madame?

218
00:14:25,992 --> 00:14:27,501
Madame?

219
00:14:31,039 --> 00:14:33,465
He's here.
The tutoring candidate.

220
00:14:37,003 --> 00:14:39,221
I don't need documents like these.

221
00:14:39,756 --> 00:14:42,307
You're here on teacher Min-hyuk's
recommendation, anyway.

222
00:14:43,009 --> 00:14:49,064
As you must know, teacher Min-hyuk
is such a "brilliant" person.

223
00:14:49,599 --> 00:14:51,834
Da-hye and my satisfaction with teacher
Min-hyuk was very high.

224
00:14:51,935 --> 00:14:55,171
...independent of her grades.
Do you know what I mean?

225
00:14:55,272 --> 00:14:56,372
Yes.

226
00:14:56,898 --> 00:14:58,549
Things were very good.

227
00:14:58,650 --> 00:15:06,089
Honestly, Da-hye and I wanted to stick with him
until her university exam next year.

228
00:15:06,408 --> 00:15:09,751
But, suddenly he tells us
he's leaving to study abroad.

229
00:15:11,913 --> 00:15:17,401
So, excuse me for being blunt,
but... honestly

230
00:15:17,502 --> 00:15:22,323
if you're not up to teacher
Min-hyuk's level, then...

231
00:15:22,424 --> 00:15:24,850
there's really no point.

232
00:15:26,886 --> 00:15:30,623
So, anyway, what I wanted to say is...

233
00:15:30,724 --> 00:15:36,378
for your first lesson today,
would you mind if I sat in?

234
00:15:36,479 --> 00:15:40,449
I want to see it "full time"
to see how you run your lessons.

235
00:15:42,485 --> 00:15:44,578
Is it okay with you?

236
00:16:12,724 --> 00:16:14,524
Are you sure about #24?

237
00:16:22,567 --> 00:16:27,179
You just spent a long while solving those
problems before going back to #24.

238
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:28,955
Right?

239
00:16:30,492 --> 00:16:31,833
Yes.

240
00:16:39,459 --> 00:16:44,930
If this was the actual exam and this the first question,
you'd be screwed from the beginning.

241
00:16:45,465 --> 00:16:49,101
Look at this. Your pulse is
pitter-pattering all over the place.

242
00:16:51,638 --> 00:16:55,065
The heart cannot lie.

243
00:16:56,309 --> 00:16:59,169
What is an exam, exactly?
It's all about cutting through.

244
00:16:59,270 --> 00:17:02,114
The flow! Lose that rhythm
and you're finished.

245
00:17:02,273 --> 00:17:04,633
The correct answer to #24?
I'm not interested.

246
00:17:04,732 --> 00:17:10,122
How you punch through the entire exam...
How you dominate it

247
00:17:10,655 --> 00:17:12,540
that's what I'm interested in.

248
00:17:13,576 --> 00:17:17,295
In real battle, it's all about the spirit.

249
00:17:18,373 --> 00:17:19,756
Spirit.

250
00:17:20,834 --> 00:17:22,259
Understand?

251
00:17:33,304 --> 00:17:36,081
Your salary will be paid out
about this time every month

252
00:17:36,182 --> 00:17:39,359
Lessons every Mon/Wed/Fri.
2 hours each. Is that okay?

253
00:17:40,211 --> 00:17:41,211
As for the amount...

254
00:17:41,312 --> 00:17:45,049
I was going to match teacher Min-hyuk's
rate but adjusted it for inflation.

