"Why are you banging someone in my car?"

525
00:34:44,208 --> 00:34:45,318
That would be silly.

526
00:34:45,418 --> 00:34:47,235
So instead...

527
00:34:47,337 --> 00:34:52,367
Can you make up some harmless excuse
and let him go quietly?

528
00:34:52,467 --> 00:34:53,826
Okay, sure.

529
00:34:53,927 --> 00:34:57,288
No need to mention panties or car sex.

530
00:34:57,389 --> 00:34:59,374
We don't need to stoop
down to that level, do we?

531
00:34:59,475 --> 00:35:01,484
Surely not!

532
00:35:02,019 --> 00:35:04,879
But, do you think driver Yoon might go online
to accuse us of wrongful termination?

533
00:35:04,980 --> 00:35:06,989
Give him a good severance package...

534
00:35:07,524 --> 00:35:10,802
You're fininshed?
Did Da-song do well today?

535
00:35:10,903 --> 00:35:12,995
Yes, of course.

536
00:35:13,530 --> 00:35:15,640
- So, lesson is finished?
- Yes.

537
00:35:15,741 --> 00:35:18,309
Teacher, the last time you came,

538
00:35:18,410 --> 00:35:20,853
our driver gave you a ride, right?

539
00:35:20,954 --> 00:35:21,813
That's right.

540
00:35:21,914 --> 00:35:24,273
This may be an awkward question,

541
00:35:24,374 --> 00:35:26,258
but nothing happened then?

542
00:35:26,376 --> 00:35:27,735
He was very friendly.

543
00:35:27,836 --> 00:35:29,696
I asked him to just drop
me off at the Hyehwa station.

544
00:35:29,797 --> 00:35:33,074
But, he kept insisting to
take me all the way home.

545
00:35:33,175 --> 00:35:36,327
That jerk, he drove all the way to
your home, so late at night?

546
00:35:36,428 --> 00:35:38,104
To reveal where you live?

547
00:35:39,139 --> 00:35:41,416
No, I got off at the Hyehwa station.

548
00:35:41,517 --> 00:35:43,876
Oh, you did well.
You did very well.

549
00:35:43,977 --> 00:35:45,545
Jessica, nice!

550
00:35:45,646 --> 00:35:48,005
Did something happen with him?

551
00:35:48,106 --> 00:35:53,302
He won't be working for us anymore.
A slightly shameful incident.

552
00:35:53,403 --> 00:35:55,346
What kind of incident?

553
00:35:55,447 --> 00:35:58,415
Teacher, enough about that.

554
00:35:59,952 --> 00:36:03,563
But I'm surprised. He was
so gentlemanly and cool.

555
00:36:03,664 --> 00:36:06,983
Jessica, you're
too young and innocent!

556
00:36:07,084 --> 00:36:09,176
You haven't experienced
a lot of people.

557
00:36:10,212 --> 00:36:14,782
But, at the time, we were excited
to have such a young, hip driver.

558
00:36:14,883 --> 00:36:18,077
But aren't drivers
better when a bit older?

559
00:36:18,178 --> 00:36:22,165
That's true! They drive better
and have better manners.

560
00:36:22,266 --> 00:36:24,917
The driver who worked for my uncle
was just like that.

561
00:36:25,018 --> 00:36:29,464
Driver Kim -- he was
so congenial and nice.

562
00:36:29,565 --> 00:36:32,091
I used to call him 'uncle' too,
when I was young.

563
00:36:32,192 --> 00:36:34,177
You know a man like that?

564
00:36:34,278 --> 00:36:37,329
Yes, he was so mild-mannered.

565
00:36:37,865 --> 00:36:42,626
Right! My uncle recently
transferred to Chicago.

566
00:36:43,704 --> 00:36:45,897
I wonder if he's currently
available.

567
00:36:45,998 --> 00:36:49,984
Very interesting !
Could I meet him, maybe?

568
00:36:50,085 --> 00:36:51,152
Oh, really?

569
00:36:51,253 --> 00:36:53,637
Nowadays, I can't trust people.

570
00:36:54,172 --> 00:36:57,074
If not recommended by someone
I know well, I really can't trust anyone.

571
00:36:57,175 --> 00:37:01,854
But, if he's some one you've seen
since you were young, that's reassuring.

572
00:37:04,433 --> 00:37:06,483
Do you really want to meet him?

573
00:37:07,019 --> 00:37:08,527
I'm deadly serious.

574
00:37:09,062 --> 00:37:12,615
Networking through
trusted referrals seems best.

575
00:37:13,150 --> 00:37:14,366
How shall I describe it?

576
00:37:14,526 --> 00:37:15,951
Safety belt of trust?

577
00:37:16,470 --> 00:37:17,470
- This one's different.
- Here.

578
00:37:17,571 --> 00:37:18,137
Oh, right.

579
00:37:18,238 --> 00:37:19,872
And this one.

580
00:37:19,990 --> 00:37:21,516
Looks like a touch screen now.

581
00:37:21,617 --> 00:37:24,519
That's not touch.
It says you have to turn it.

582
00:37:24,620 --> 00:37:26,670
Wow, this thing?

583
00:37:27,105 --> 00:37:28,105
Sir?

584
00:37:28,206 --> 00:37:30,549
You're taking your time?

585
00:37:33,147 --> 00:37:34,976
This is a nice car.

586
00:37:37,925 --> 00:37:39,141
Here it is!
Come over here.

587
00:37:42,846 --> 00:37:44,396
He's in a meeting now.

588
00:37:49,436 --> 00:37:51,445
Have a seat and wait here.

589
00:38:00,072 --> 00:38:03,540
How do you do?
Nice to meet...

590
00:38:06,662 --> 00:38:08,145
But, is it compatible
with mobile phones?

591
00:38:08,246 --> 00:38:14,927
These are not compatible.
Requires more computing power.

592
00:38:16,046 --> 00:38:20,683
This isn't a test drive or anything,
so don't be nervous.

593
00:38:21,426 --> 00:38:24,478
I came out because I felt
so couped up at the office all day.

594
00:38:25,013 --> 00:38:26,163
I understand.

595
00:38:26,264 --> 00:38:30,859
Constant chatter, all that bother.
At least, the car should offer some peace.

596
00:38:33,271 --> 00:38:34,571
Thank you.

597
00:38:35,607 --> 00:38:36,799
You seem to know the roads very well?

598
00:38:36,900 --> 00:38:40,219
Below the 38th parallel, I know
all the roads and side streets.

599
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:43,580
It comes naturally
after 30 years behind the wheel.

600
00:38:44,116 --> 00:38:46,750
I respect those who work
in a single field for a long time.

601
00:38:46,994 --> 00:38:49,979
Well, to be honest
this may be a simple vocation.

602
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:53,090
But, to get on the road every morning
with the head of a household

603
00:38:53,625 --> 00:38:54,775
or with the company's
commander-in-chief

604
00:38:54,876 --> 00:39:00,389
or with just a solitary man
each and every morning...

605
00:39:01,258 --> 00:39:03,017
it's a companionship of a sort.

606
00:39:03,176 --> 00:39:06,078
So, that's been my approach
each and every day.

607
00:39:06,179 --> 00:39:08,063
The years sure pass quickly.

608
00:39:11,768 --> 00:39:14,403
Sure enough,
your cornering is superb.

609
00:39:15,105 --> 00:39:21,469
Well, the fundamentals
may look easy, but...

610
00:39:21,570 --> 00:39:26,332
May look sheepish, but
inside she's a crafty old fox.

611
00:39:26,450 --> 00:39:29,543
Sometimes she acts like
she owns the house!

612
00:39:30,062 --> 00:39:31,062
Right.

613
00:39:31,163 --> 00:39:35,650
She's lived there longer
than anyone in that house.

614
00:39:35,751 --> 00:39:39,403
She was the housekeeper
to that architect, Nam-goong.

615
00:39:39,504 --> 00:39:44,183
But then, she stayed on
to work for this family.

616
00:39:44,718 --> 00:39:46,077
When Mr. Nam-goong moved out,

617
00:39:46,178 --> 00:39:49,080
he introduced that woman to
Mr. and Mrs. Park, telling them...

618
00:39:49,181 --> 00:39:52,524
"She takes great care of this house.
You should keep her!"

619
00:39:52,642 --> 00:39:55,962
So, this is the case where the house ownership
changed, but not the housekeeper.

620
00:39:56,063 --> 00:39:59,114
She's holding tight to this good job
and not letting go.

621
00:39:59,649 --> 00:40:02,785
To surgically remove a woman like that,
we need some preparation.

622
00:40:04,488 --> 00:40:06,830
Right, we need a plan.

623
00:40:07,866 --> 00:40:11,418
I want some peaches.
I like peaches best.

624
00:40:11,953 --> 00:40:13,062
Why not ask for some?

625
00:40:13,163 --> 00:40:16,924
No peaches allowed in our home
- - forbidden fruit.

626
00:40:24,591 --> 00:40:27,451
According to what
I heard from Da-hye,

627
00:40:27,552 --> 00:40:32,164
she has a massively
serious allergy to peaches.

628
00:40:32,265 --> 00:40:35,501
You know all that
fuzz on the skin?

629
00:40:35,602 --> 00:40:39,213
If she goes anywhere near it,
she breaks out in hives

630
00:40:39,314 --> 00:40:43,283
has trouble breathing,
asthma, a total meltdown!

631
00:40:47,823 --> 00:40:51,959
No, no, no. No peaches anywhere
and it still happened.

632
00:40:53,620 --> 00:40:56,088
That's what I'm saying!

633
00:40:56,331 --> 00:40:58,816
Usually when I get symptoms like this

634
00:40:58,917 --> 00:41:02,319
I run to my room and
medication takes care of it.

635
00:41:02,420 --> 00:41:07,783
This was so sudden, I panicked and
couldn't remember where I put it!

636
00:41:07,884 --> 00:41:12,913
Madame, this woman behind me,
is that...?

637
00:41:13,014 --> 00:41:14,915
Oh, my! That's our housekeeper!

638
00:41:15,016 --> 00:41:17,668
Then it's true!
Oh, what should I do?

639
00:41:17,769 --> 00:41:20,755
I wasn't sure if that was really her.

640
00:41:20,856 --> 00:41:24,616
I've only seen her a couple of times
in the living room.

641
00:41:25,152 --> 00:41:27,136
You took this in a hospital?

642
00:41:27,237 --> 00:41:31,165
A few days ago,
I went for my annual checkup.

643
00:41:31,700 --> 00:41:35,711
I took a selfie for my wife,
and there she was, right behind me.

644
00:41:36,204 --> 00:41:38,213
She's talking to someone on the phone?

645
00:41:38,415 --> 00:41:43,569
I wasn't trying to eavesdrop...

646
00:41:43,670 --> 00:41:45,488
but because I could hear her conversation!

647
00:41:45,589 --> 00:41:47,323
- I couldn't help but...
- Cut, cut!

648
00:41:47,424 --> 00:41:50,284
Father, your emotion is
too far up to here.

649
00:41:50,385 --> 00:41:52,644
Bring it down to about here.

650
00:41:53,180 --> 00:41:55,623
I couldn't help but overhear.

651
00:41:55,724 --> 00:41:58,484
Compress it, then... boom!

652
00:42:00,020 --> 00:42:02,296
What I'm trying to say is,
it's just that...

653
00:42:02,397 --> 00:42:06,617
her voice was quite loud!

654
00:42:06,776 --> 00:42:10,304
It's alright.
Just tell me, okay?

655
00:42:10,405 --> 00:42:13,224
She said she just got
diagnosed with Active TB.

656
00:42:13,325 --> 00:42:15,392
And was shouting
about it on the phone

657
00:42:15,493 --> 00:42:18,562
as if so upset with herself,
she could hardly control herself!

658
00:42:18,663 --> 00:42:20,981
Tuberculosis? Surely...

659
00:42:21,082 --> 00:42:26,428
It's true! She was telling someone
on the phone that she had Active TB.

660
00:42:26,963 --> 00:42:31,558
"Oh my! Do people still get TB these days?"
Oh my! Do people still get TB these days?

661
00:42:31,752 --> 00:42:32,852
"Dad : "

662
00:42:33,094 --> 00:42:38,082
"True... in the old days, people
used to buy Christmas seals for this."

663
00:42:38,183 --> 00:42:39,500
"Feels like something from a bygone era..."

664
00:42:39,601 --> 00:42:41,252
Search it on the internet.

665
00:42:41,353 --> 00:42:45,172
Korea ranks # 1 for TB
among of all OECD countries.

666
00:42:45,273 --> 00:42:48,801
"She was working, pretending
as if nothing was wrong !"

667
00:42:48,902 --> 00:42:50,845
"With young children in the house
like Da-song."

668
00:42:50,946 --> 00:42:54,223
And, with young children
in the house like Da-song.

669
00:42:54,324 --> 00:42:57,560
A TB patient is doing dishes, preparing
food and coughing up bodily fluids...

670
00:42:57,661 --> 00:42:59,294
Stop it, please!

671
00:43:52,132 --> 00:43:56,143
If we get the chance,
this will be the finishing touch.

672
00:44:41,556 --> 00:44:43,148
- Have a seat
- Yes.

673
00:44:45,293 --> 00:44:46,293
Driver Kim.

674
00:44:46,394 --> 00:44:50,464
Please don't tell any of this
to my kids or my husband, okay?

675
00:44:50,565 --> 00:44:51,590
I understand.

676
00:44:51,691 --> 00:44:56,370
If he hears I've harboured
a TB patient in our home

677
00:44:56,529 --> 00:44:59,265
I'll be hanged and quartered!

678
00:44:59,366 --> 00:45:01,267
Don't worry, Madame.

679
00:45:01,368 --> 00:45:04,979
And if I may please say one thing

680
00:45:05,080 --> 00:45:08,382
I have no hard feelings
against that woman.

681
00:45:08,917 --> 00:45:16,006
I merely felt I had to speak up from
the perspective of public health and safety.

682
00:45:16,383 --> 00:45:19,910
This could be misconstrued
as snitching...

683
00:45:20,011 --> 00:45:21,412
You don't have to worry about that.

684
00:45:21,513 --> 00:45:24,081
I'm not going to mention TB to her.

685
00:45:24,182 --> 00:45:26,625
I'll just make up some other
excuse and dismiss her.

686
00:45:26,726 --> 00:45:28,235
Simply and quietly.

687
00:45:29,854 --> 00:45:32,548
It's the proven way.
This is the best way.

688
00:45:32,649 --> 00:45:34,574
Well, then.

689
00:45:46,719 --> 00:45:51,164
You...
washed your hands?

690
00:46:34,294 --> 00:46:38,364
Driver Kim, do you know
a good braised-galbi place?

691
00:46:38,465 --> 00:46:40,115
Not too far away.
Somewhere near by?

692
00:46:40,216 --> 00:46:41,575
Sure.

693
00:46:41,676 --> 00:46:45,437
- Then you'll be eating out?
- That's right.

694
00:46:46,055 --> 00:46:48,982
Not sure why the craving
for braised-galbi today.

695
00:46:49,517 --> 00:46:52,402
Our housekeeper used to make
really good braised ribs.

696
00:46:53,438 --> 00:46:55,506
The one who quit
the day before yesterday?

697
00:46:55,607 --> 00:47:00,577
My wife wouldn't even tell me why she quit.

698
00:47:03,198 --> 00:47:08,585
Then again, housekeepers are plentiful.
We could just hire a new one.

699
00:47:09,621 --> 00:47:14,233
Still, it's a shame.
She was a very good housekeeper.

700
00:47:14,334 --> 00:47:15,234
I see.

701
00:47:15,335 --> 00:47:17,903
She kept every corner
of the house in great shape.

702
00:47:18,004 --> 00:47:20,680
And she knew
never to cross the line.

703
00:47:21,216 --> 00:47:24,100
I can't stand people
who cross the line.

704
00:47:24,636 --> 00:47:27,312
If just one negative point...

705
00:47:27,931 --> 00:47:29,415
eating too much?

706
00:47:29,516 --> 00:47:32,442
She said she always ate two servings.

707
00:47:33,102 --> 00:47:36,964
Then again, she does do a lot of work.

708
00:47:37,065 --> 00:47:42,428
Then she'd better find someone
quickly. A new housekeeper.

709
00:47:42,529 --> 00:47:44,555
She's in big trouble right now.

710
00:47:44,656 --> 00:47:49,125
With that housekeeper, our
house will be trashed in a week.

711
00:47:50,161 --> 00:47:53,171
My clothes will start to reek...

712
00:47:54,207 --> 00:47:57,109
My wife never had any talent for housework.

713
00:47:57,210 --> 00:48:00,512
She's bad at cleaning,
and her cooking's god-awful.

714
00:48:01,548 --> 00:48:03,431
You still love her, right?

715
00:48:11,099 --> 00:48:14,442
Of course, I love her.

716
00:48:15,478 --> 00:48:17,362
You have to call that love.

717
00:48:18,982 --> 00:48:21,157
Then, take this.

718
00:48:25,196 --> 00:48:27,389
THE CARE?
What is this?

719
00:48:27,490 --> 00:48:29,975
I found out about them
just recently.

720
00:48:30,076 --> 00:48:34,921
How to describe it?
It's a members-only service.

721
00:48:35,498 --> 00:48:42,029
Provides experienced maids, caregivers
and drivers like myself to VIP customers like you.

722
00:48:42,130 --> 00:48:48,035
A professional service of carefully
selected experts in their fields.

723
00:48:48,136 --> 00:48:51,354
You can tell they're very exclusive
even from the card.

724
00:48:51,889 --> 00:48:53,481
The design, too.

725
00:48:54,559 --> 00:48:56,543
Driver Kim, how did you
come across this company?

726
00:48:56,644 --> 00:49:01,173
They contacted me, because
of my veteran-status as VIP driver.

727
00:49:01,274 --> 00:49:03,491
A kind of a scout offer?

728
00:49:05,028 --> 00:49:10,766
But, when I got their call, I was already
scheduled to interview with you.

729
00:49:10,867 --> 00:49:14,044
I see...

730
00:49:15,079 --> 00:49:18,745
Your grace for turning down work with such a
prestigious company to work for me...

731
00:49:18,875 --> 00:49:20,300
I'm forever indebted.

732
00:49:21,836 --> 00:49:24,054
Fuck!

733
00:49:26,090 --> 00:49:29,952
Anyway, I can give
this card to my wife, right?

734
00:49:30,053 --> 00:49:31,828
Yes, that's why I brought it up.

735
00:49:31,929 --> 00:49:34,105
No need to mention me.

736
00:49:35,516 --> 00:49:38,693
You can tell her that you
found the company yourself.

737
00:49:39,228 --> 00:49:40,587
Sure, why not.

738
00:49:40,688 --> 00:49:43,048
Thanks to you I can
play the good husband.

739
00:49:43,149 --> 00:49:47,928
On the back, there's a
number for consultations.

740
00:49:48,029 --> 00:49:49,179
Tell her to call that...

741
00:49:49,280 --> 00:49:50,830
Eyes on the road!

742
00:49:55,870 --> 00:49:59,089
Hello, this is The Care's
senior advisor, Yeo Myung-son.

743
00:49:59,248 --> 00:50:02,717
Yes, is this The Care's main office?

744
00:50:03,503 --> 00:50:06,905
She's going to be very successful,
even as a con artist.

745
00:50:07,006 --> 00:50:09,641
Isn't the tone of her voice great?
Takes after me.

746
00:50:11,177 --> 00:50:13,704
From what I've heard,
it's a members-only service?

747
00:50:13,805 --> 00:50:17,666
So, you're not currently
a member, I assume?

748
00:50:17,767 --> 00:50:20,294
That's right. What steps
do I need to take?

749
00:50:20,395 --> 00:50:24,506
We will need just a few documents.

750
00:50:24,607 --> 00:50:27,593
Are you ready to write this down?

751
00:50:27,694 --> 00:50:32,580
Your family register,
copy of your family's ID cards...

