1495
01:48:40,683 --> 01:48:44,419
- No, not yet.
- Shouldn't we have a talk with them?

1496
01:48:44,520 --> 01:48:46,338
In a way that is
good for everyone?

1497
01:48:46,439 --> 01:48:47,380
Exactly!

1498
01:48:47,481 --> 01:48:50,258
We all got too fucking
worked up last night!

1499
01:48:50,359 --> 01:48:54,287
I know! And, dad was going on
about some plan...

1500
01:48:54,697 --> 01:48:57,140
- No, I'm going down there now.
- Hold on!

1501
01:48:57,241 --> 01:48:59,434
Take this down to them.

1502
01:48:59,535 --> 01:49:01,144
- They must be hungry.
- Right.

1503
01:49:01,245 --> 01:49:03,213
Let them eat first.

1504
01:49:05,124 --> 01:49:06,758
Come next time for sure!

1505
01:49:07,793 --> 01:49:09,528
Here you are, Jessica.

1506
01:49:09,629 --> 01:49:11,988
- This is too good !
- Yes, to die for!

1507
01:49:12,089 --> 01:49:14,574
I've got a special favor to ask.

1508
01:49:14,675 --> 01:49:15,850
What kind?

1509
01:49:16,093 --> 01:49:18,161
This is...
how to describe it?

1510
01:49:18,262 --> 01:49:20,205
Da-song's trauma
recovery cake?

1511
01:49:20,306 --> 01:49:23,775
So, it needs to be you who does this.
Today's highlight!

1512
01:50:46,726 --> 01:50:50,111
Excuse me...
Are you ok?

1513
01:50:55,151 --> 01:50:56,659
Excuse me...

1514
01:51:06,704 --> 01:51:08,004
Mister! Mister!

1515
01:52:55,020 --> 01:52:58,030
Oppa? Oppa?

1516
01:53:04,572 --> 01:53:07,307
Da-song !
Happy birthday!

1517
01:53:07,408 --> 01:53:08,875
Congratulations!

1518
01:53:16,128 --> 01:53:17,554
Oh, fuck!

1519
01:53:27,229 --> 01:53:29,329
Stop!!

1520
01:53:29,430 --> 01:53:31,539
Sister Chung-sook!

1521
01:53:31,640 --> 01:53:32,415
Ki-jung!

1522
01:53:32,516 --> 01:53:34,125
Come on out, Chung-sook!

1523
01:53:34,226 --> 01:53:37,636
Stop the bleeding!
Push down on the wound!

1524
01:53:42,098 --> 01:53:43,533
Da-song!

1525
01:53:44,189 --> 01:53:45,408
Honey!

1526
01:53:46,590 --> 01:53:48,315
Let go!
Don't do it!

1527
01:53:59,666 --> 01:54:01,429
It hurts!

1528
01:54:05,927 --> 01:54:07,117
The ER!

1529
01:54:07,218 --> 01:54:08,751
Get the car out!
The car!

1530
01:54:08,852 --> 01:54:10,395
Driver Kim !
What the fuck are you doing?!

1531
01:54:10,496 --> 01:54:12,622
If we wait for the ambulance,
it'll be too late!

1532
01:54:12,723 --> 01:54:15,133
Dad, dad!
Stop pressing it.

1533
01:54:15,234 --> 01:54:18,194
Pressing it makes it
hurt more.

1534
01:54:18,854 --> 01:54:20,004
Give me the car key!
The car key!

1535
01:54:20,105 --> 01:54:22,922
Throw them !
Just throw me the key!

1536
01:54:40,542 --> 01:54:42,118
You okay?

1537
01:54:42,219 --> 01:54:44,220
Don't touch it!
Don't touch it!

1538
01:54:46,291 --> 01:54:48,808
How do you do, Mr. Park?

1539
01:54:48,926 --> 01:54:49,993
You know me?

1540
01:54:50,094 --> 01:54:51,769
Respect!

1541
01:56:18,432 --> 01:56:21,793
A month later when I opened my eyes,
the first face that I saw...

1542
01:56:21,894 --> 01:56:23,694
was that of a detective.

1543
01:56:23,854 --> 01:56:28,633
You have the right to an attorney...

1544
01:56:28,734 --> 01:56:31,035
He looked nothing
like a detective.

1545
01:56:35,574 --> 01:56:37,267
Is he laughing?

1546
01:56:37,368 --> 01:56:39,043
Just a moment.

1547
01:56:39,453 --> 01:56:44,298
Then, the doctor who looked
nothing like a doctor spoke.

1548
01:56:45,334 --> 01:56:49,112
That happens sometimes
immediately after brain surgery.

1549
01:56:49,213 --> 01:56:51,430
They keep laughing
for no reason.

1550
01:56:52,091 --> 01:56:54,308
Can you hear me?

1551
01:56:54,551 --> 01:56:56,435
Can you hear me, now?

1552
01:56:56,553 --> 01:56:58,329
Then, we have to do it again?

1553
01:56:58,430 --> 01:56:59,247
Do what again?

1554
01:56:59,348 --> 01:57:00,898
What I just did.
The Miranda.

1555
01:57:03,435 --> 01:57:07,255
You ! Um... have the right!
To remain silent!

1556
01:57:07,356 --> 01:57:10,091
Anything you say can and will
be used against you ...right? ...and

1557
01:57:10,192 --> 01:57:12,576
He keeps laughing, look!

1558
01:57:15,614 --> 01:57:21,711
Even when I heard how much
Ki-jung bled that day

1559
01:57:23,872 --> 01:57:31,087
even when I heard the words "document forgery,"
"trespassing," "foul play, but self-defense"

1560
01:57:31,338 --> 01:57:35,725
...and that we were lucky to get away
with just a probation...

1561
01:57:38,762 --> 01:57:41,789
even when I finally got to
see Ki-jung's face...

1562
01:57:41,890 --> 01:57:44,900
Kim Ki-jung
Nov 20, 1996 -- July 1,2018

1563
01:57:46,437 --> 01:57:48,738
I kept laughing.

1564
01:57:58,407 --> 01:58:03,895
But, when I looked back
and watched all the news reports

1565
01:58:03,996 --> 01:58:05,188
I didn't laugh much at all.

1566
01:58:57,549 --> 01:59:04,514
Mom and I actually had no idea
where father was.

1567
01:59:06,850 --> 01:59:12,530
But, those detectives trying to tail us
still wore themselves out.

1568
01:59:16,568 --> 01:59:22,540
Eventually, when the news went quiet, and
the taills became less frequent

1569
01:59:23,075 --> 01:59:26,502
I started, from time to time,
to go up that mountain.

1570
01:59:28,539 --> 01:59:33,259
From up there, you get
a good view of the house.

1571
01:59:36,004 --> 01:59:43,135
That day, despite the cold,
I felt the urge to stay behind longer.

1572
01:59:56,483 --> 01:59:59,994
Dash - dash - dot - dot

1573
02:00:04,023 --> 02:00:07,491
dot - dot - dot - dash
dash - dash - dot...

1574
02:00:28,536 --> 02:00:29,878
Son!

1575
02:00:31,852 --> 02:00:35,696
You may be able to read this letter.

1576
02:00:39,234 --> 02:00:45,539
You were a Boy Scout, so just in case,
I am writing you a letter this way.

1577
02:00:48,577 --> 02:00:51,545
Have you recovered ok
from your injuries?

1578
02:00:52,581 --> 02:00:56,884
I'm sure your mom is
plenty healthy.

1579
02:01:00,922 --> 02:01:03,724
I'm doing fine
down here.

1580
02:01:04,760 --> 02:01:07,519
Though, I often cry
thinking bout Ki-jung.

1581
02:01:10,557 --> 02:01:15,402
Even now, what happened
that day seems surreal.

1582
02:01:16,647 --> 02:01:18,364
Feels like I dreamt it all.

1583
02:01:19,900 --> 02:01:21,867
Maybe I didn't.

1584
02:01:22,903 --> 02:01:27,873
That day, as I ran out the gate,
I suddenly realized

1585
02:01:28,909 --> 02:01:30,668
where I needed to go.

1586
02:02:10,075 --> 02:02:13,060
A house where such
grisly crime took place

1587
02:02:13,161 --> 02:02:16,422
is surely not so easy to sell.

1588
02:02:19,543 --> 02:02:21,944
I'm so sorry, Mr. Park.

1589
02:02:22,045 --> 02:02:28,600
So, I struggled to hold out in the
empty house until the new owners arrived.

1590
02:02:31,138 --> 02:02:34,040
Still, thanks to the
house being empty

1591
02:02:34,141 --> 02:02:39,003
What was her name?
'Moon' and 'Gwang?'

1592
02:02:39,104 --> 02:02:43,407
I was able to give lady Moon-gwang
a proper, dignified send off.

1593
02:02:44,526 --> 02:02:51,290
I gave her a tree-side burial which I hear are very
trendy these days. So, hell, I did my best.

1594
02:02:54,828 --> 02:02:58,464
But, those real estate sharks
sure are clever.

1595
02:03:03,003 --> 02:03:07,239
They hoodwinked some people
newly arrived in Korea and knowing nothing

1596
02:03:07,340 --> 02:03:09,683
and ultimately managed to
sell them the house.

1597
02:03:10,802 --> 02:03:14,080
With the parents working in a foreign company
and the kids attending a foreign school,

1598
02:03:14,181 --> 02:03:16,774
the family is usually out.

1599
02:03:16,892 --> 02:03:22,321
But, the goddamned housekeeper
stays glued here 24 hours a day.

1600
02:03:22,481 --> 02:03:27,409
Each time I go upstairs to the kitchen,
I put my life on the line.

1601
02:03:29,946 --> 02:03:34,291
It turns out that Germans don't eat and
drink just sausages and beer.

1602
02:03:34,826 --> 02:03:36,877
What a relief.

1603
02:03:39,456 --> 02:03:43,842
Passing the time down here,
everything starts to go hazy.

1604
02:03:48,381 --> 02:03:52,559
Today, at least, I was able to
write you a letter.

1605
02:03:54,095 --> 02:03:57,998
If I send out the letter
this way every night

1606
02:03:58,099 --> 02:04:02,569
maybe someday
you'll see it.

1607
02:04:08,610 --> 02:04:10,661
So long for now.

1608
02:04:24,209 --> 02:04:25,276
Ki-woo?
Is that you?

1609
02:04:25,377 --> 02:04:26,477
Yes.

1610
02:04:40,892 --> 02:04:45,904
Father,
I made a plan today.

1611
02:04:47,440 --> 02:04:49,366
It's a master plan.

1612
02:04:52,404 --> 02:04:54,079
I'm going to make money.

1613
02:04:54,656 --> 02:04:56,456
...loads of it.

1614
02:04:59,995 --> 02:05:04,506
University, career, marriage,
they're all fine

1615
02:05:04,666 --> 02:05:06,692
but I will first make money.

1616
02:05:06,793 --> 02:05:12,139
You'll see once you go in,
but it's very spacious.

1617
02:05:12,674 --> 02:05:17,411
Actually, we don't show
this kind of house to just anyone.

1618
02:05:17,512 --> 02:05:22,024
When I make the money,
I will first buy this house.

1619
02:05:23,059 --> 02:05:27,321
On the day we move in,
Mom and I will be in the garden.

1620
02:05:27,856 --> 02:05:30,282
Because the sunshine
is so nice there.

1621
02:05:31,443 --> 02:05:33,493
All you have to do

1622
02:05:33,653 --> 02:05:36,538
is come up the stairs.

1623
02:06:59,155 --> 02:07:03,292
Until that day comes, please
take very good care of yourself.

1624
02:07:07,956 --> 02:07:10,090
So long for now.

